WEBVTT

00:07.807 --> 00:08.774
[CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08.808 --> 00:10.744
[VENDOR SPEAKING
OTHER LANGUGAE]

00:12.878 --> 00:14.414
[NIKOLAI SPEAKING NORWEGIAN]

00:24.657 --> 00:27.293
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

00:33.500 --> 00:35.368
[BIRDS CAWING]

00:50.616 --> 00:52.018
[IN ENGLISH] Come on!

00:52.051 --> 00:53.653
[NIKOLAI SPEAKING NORWEGIAN]

01:00.693 --> 01:02.829
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:16.075 --> 01:17.577
[UTENSILS RATTLING]

01:17.610 --> 01:18.611
[SOFT THUD]

01:21.214 --> 01:23.216
[STEAM WHISTLING]

01:38.564 --> 01:40.300
[WHOOSHING]

01:38.564 --> 01:40.300
[SILENCED GUNSHOTS]

01:43.903 --> 01:45.705
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

01:48.274 --> 01:49.742
[WHISTLING STOPS]

01:54.046 --> 01:56.683
[SOFT DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

02:04.223 --> 02:06.659
Come on, come on, come on.

02:08.161 --> 02:10.196
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:17.069 --> 02:18.404
[WHOOSHING]

02:19.205 --> 02:21.774
You look like shit.
Have you slept?

02:21.807 --> 02:23.376
It's bad.
This is bad.

02:23.409 --> 02:26.445
They found me, I think.

02:26.478 --> 02:28.714
I don't know anymore.

02:26.478 --> 02:28.714
I can't be here.

02:28.748 --> 02:30.049
If they tracked you...

02:30.082 --> 02:31.684
Jesus, you know better.

02:31.717 --> 02:33.385
No, wait, wait, please.

02:33.419 --> 02:34.753
We promised
to help each other.

02:34.787 --> 02:37.523
If we both go public,
we can shut them down.

02:37.557 --> 02:39.425
No.

02:37.557 --> 02:39.425
No, Fatima, please.

02:39.459 --> 02:41.393
It's the only way
I can protect my family.

02:41.427 --> 02:43.729
Hank, she...

02:41.427 --> 02:43.729
You want to protect
your daughter?

02:43.763 --> 02:44.831
Keep your distance.

02:47.267 --> 02:48.568
I'm her father.

02:49.902 --> 02:51.737
We all make sacrifices.

02:51.770 --> 02:52.639
[WHOOSHING]

02:56.342 --> 02:58.845
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

03:05.718 --> 03:09.489
I've been thinking a lot lately
about what makes a family.

03:10.056 --> 03:11.958
Is it genetics?

03:12.725 --> 03:16.862
Or is it sharing a home?

03:16.896 --> 03:21.400
Or is it facing challenges
head-on together?

03:21.434 --> 03:22.936
And I think it's that one.

03:22.969 --> 03:25.805
The... I think
it's that last one.

03:25.838 --> 03:30.042
'Cause, hey, nobody can deny
that we have experienced

03:30.075 --> 03:33.346
a lot of highs
and a lot of lows lately.

03:34.079 --> 03:36.516
Mostly lows.

03:37.517 --> 03:41.487
But if, um, being a family

03:41.520 --> 03:45.324
is really about how we tackle

03:45.358 --> 03:49.128
those big problems,

03:49.161 --> 03:52.098
those problems, then...
Which I...

03:52.131 --> 03:55.268
you know, as I said,
I think it is...

03:55.301 --> 03:57.303
then check, please.
[CHUCKLES]

03:59.204 --> 04:01.106
[SIGHS]

04:01.139 --> 04:02.742
Is this about
marrying my mom?

04:04.877 --> 04:06.546
Yeah, it... yes, it is.

04:06.579 --> 04:10.382
And, um,
I would really love,

04:10.416 --> 04:12.252
I mean,
both of your blessings.

04:13.585 --> 04:15.788
You know she's still married
to my dad, right?

04:16.322 --> 04:18.224
I do know that.

04:18.257 --> 04:19.425
But your mom
is getting a divorce.

04:19.458 --> 04:21.894
We've started the process.

04:21.927 --> 04:23.997
I'm sorry, Henry.
I thought she told you.

04:26.099 --> 04:27.433
Do whatever you want.

04:29.335 --> 04:31.271
Why are you doing this now?

04:32.405 --> 04:33.539
In front of her?

04:33.572 --> 04:35.441
Were you worried
I would freak out?

04:36.975 --> 04:38.410
I...

04:38.444 --> 04:40.580
I thought it was important
to discuss it as a family.

04:42.047 --> 04:44.083
But this isn't a discussion.

04:44.116 --> 04:45.384
It's an announcement,

04:45.417 --> 04:47.320
like when you announced
that they were moving in.

04:47.753 --> 04:49.021
I can go.

04:49.054 --> 04:52.258
No, Henry, please stay.

04:52.291 --> 04:53.492
It's only been three years.

04:53.526 --> 04:55.461
Oh, sweetheart, it's not...

04:55.495 --> 04:57.664
Are you gonna give her
mom's ring, too?

04:58.297 --> 05:00.366
Uh, of... No.

05:00.399 --> 05:02.268
I would never do that.
That is your ring...

05:02.301 --> 05:03.770
That's yours
for when you get married.

05:05.838 --> 05:07.006
Right.

05:07.907 --> 05:08.941
Jenna.

05:08.975 --> 05:10.677
Je... [SIGHS]

05:11.644 --> 05:15.014
Jenna, can we just
start this again?

05:15.614 --> 05:18.084
Darling, listen...
Jenna.

05:19.551 --> 05:21.954
[ELECTRONIC POP MUSIC PLAYING]

05:24.357 --> 05:27.327
<i> ♪ It's been way</i>

05:27.827 --> 05:29.729
<i> ♪ Too long</i>

05:32.497 --> 05:35.735
<i> ♪ Never thought she</i>

05:35.768 --> 05:37.837
<i> ♪ Was wrong</i>

05:40.272 --> 05:41.874
<i> ♪ What else</i>

05:43.042 --> 05:46.412
<i> ♪ She had said</i>

05:48.314 --> 05:50.049
<i> ♪ You were</i>

05:51.083 --> 05:53.920
<i> ♪ Poison to her head</i>

05:57.223 --> 05:58.758
[MUSIC CONTINUES FAINTLY
OVER HEADPHONES]

06:13.572 --> 06:15.441
<i> ♪ It has been way ♪</i>

06:15.475 --> 06:17.043
[MUSIC STOPS]

06:26.518 --> 06:28.855
<i> [SECRET MEETING</i> PLAYING]

06:34.226 --> 06:37.363
<i> ♪ I think this place</i>

06:37.396 --> 06:40.499
<i> ♪ Is full of spies</i>

06:40.532 --> 06:43.869
<i> ♪ I think they're onto me</i>

06:43.903 --> 06:47.373
<i> ♪ Didn't anybody,
Didn't anybody tell you</i>

06:47.406 --> 06:49.608
<i> ♪ Didn't anybody tell you</i>

06:49.641 --> 06:51.878
<i> ♪ How to gracefully
Disappear in a room</i>

07:00.485 --> 07:03.522
<i> ♪ I know you
Put in the hours</i>

07:03.555 --> 07:08.494
<i> ♪ To keep me in sunglasses,
I know</i>

07:08.527 --> 07:13.132
<i> ♪ And so and now
I'm sorry I missed you</i>

07:13.165 --> 07:15.134
<i> ♪ I had a secret meeting</i>

07:15.167 --> 07:18.771
<i>♪ In the basement of my brain</i>

07:21.974 --> 07:26.779
<i> ♪ It went the dull and
Wicked ordinary way</i>

07:30.149 --> 07:33.285
<i> ♪ It went the dull and
Wicked ordinary way ♪</i>

07:33.319 --> 07:34.720
Holy shit.

07:36.922 --> 07:39.625
ANNA: Thank you
for coming over
to talk, I appreciate it.

07:39.658 --> 07:42.428
CLEO: No, it's nice
to get out of the house.

07:42.462 --> 07:45.998
I heard about what happened,
you know, with the car.

07:46.599 --> 07:48.267
Is everything okay?

07:48.301 --> 07:50.336
Well, they're saying
I'm crazy, right?

07:50.369 --> 07:52.538
Oh, people talk a lot
in this town.

07:52.571 --> 07:54.340
Most of it's bullshit.

07:54.373 --> 07:55.474
Half of them still think

07:55.507 --> 07:56.609
Bill Boone and I
were sleeping together.

07:56.642 --> 07:58.844
[CHUCKLES]
Now, that's crazy.

07:58.877 --> 08:00.045
Thank you.

08:00.078 --> 08:01.847
Also, ew.

08:01.880 --> 08:03.782
[CHUCKLES]

08:03.815 --> 08:08.087
Actually, I did want to ask
about Bill, if that's okay.

08:08.120 --> 08:09.755
About what happened.

08:08.120 --> 08:09.755
Okay.

08:09.789 --> 08:10.756
Um...

08:13.859 --> 08:16.863
So we found his blood
in your dining room,

08:17.997 --> 08:20.399
and it looks like somebody
tried to clean it up.

08:20.432 --> 08:22.034
Uh, what does that mean?

08:23.135 --> 08:25.638
I was hoping
you could tell me.

08:25.671 --> 08:29.241
I don't know.
I was too busy bleeding out
on the dining room floor.

08:29.274 --> 08:31.176
Cleo, I have to ask
these things.

08:31.210 --> 08:32.712
Do you anymore?

08:33.379 --> 08:35.281
It's late.
I should go.

08:38.584 --> 08:40.086
What about Henry?

08:42.888 --> 08:45.057
I'm not doing this
to torture you, I swear.

08:45.992 --> 08:47.760
I think about that day
all the time,

08:48.460 --> 08:50.897
how I should have stopped it.

08:52.064 --> 08:53.299
But this blood suggests

08:53.332 --> 08:55.467
something more complicated
happened,

08:55.500 --> 08:57.436
maybe more than you even know.

08:57.469 --> 08:59.771
So, what, you think
Henry's lying to me?

08:59.805 --> 09:02.575
A lot of her story
doesn't make sense.

09:02.608 --> 09:06.711
I mean, if Bill was violent
with her after you

09:06.745 --> 09:09.081
or if Henry had to act
in self-defense or...

09:09.114 --> 09:10.783
Do you think
he might have hurt her?

09:11.484 --> 09:12.618
I don't know.

09:14.252 --> 09:17.256
And she did what?

09:17.289 --> 09:18.457
Henry did what?

09:18.491 --> 09:20.893
I'm not sure, but when
I spoke to Clay, he...

09:20.926 --> 09:22.761
Clay? You talked
to Clay Boone?

09:22.794 --> 09:24.463
Why would you talk to him?
He doesn't know what happened.

09:24.496 --> 09:26.365
Just doing my job,
pursuing leads.

09:26.398 --> 09:29.768
God, that kid, that fucking
family won't leave us alone.

09:29.802 --> 09:31.937
I mean, how is she supposed
to move on, huh?

09:31.971 --> 09:34.706
I mean, did you see him?
He's on TV praising his dad,

09:34.740 --> 09:36.609
who's an attempted
fucking murderer.

09:36.642 --> 09:38.210
I mean, it's so sick.

09:38.243 --> 09:39.679
I know.

09:41.013 --> 09:43.415
But if something happened
in that house

09:43.449 --> 09:45.150
that Henry has kept from us,

09:45.184 --> 09:47.219
I want to know why.

09:47.252 --> 09:48.320
Because if I don't,

09:48.353 --> 09:50.056
I can't help her.

09:50.089 --> 09:52.058
Neither can you.

09:52.091 --> 09:54.493
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

09:54.526 --> 09:57.629
<i> ♪ I'm the new blue blood</i>

09:57.663 --> 10:00.966
<i> ♪ I'm the great white hope</i>

10:00.999 --> 10:05.071
<i> ♪ I'm the new,
I'm the new, I'm the new</i>

10:05.671 --> 10:08.107
[MUSIC SKIPPING]

10:08.707 --> 10:10.876
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

10:10.909 --> 10:13.346
<i> ♪ I'm the new blue blood ♪</i>

10:18.650 --> 10:20.953
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

10:28.227 --> 10:29.561
Mom?

10:28.227 --> 10:29.561
[GASPS]

10:29.594 --> 10:31.163
Oh, my God.

10:32.131 --> 10:33.265
You scared me, Henry.

10:38.770 --> 10:41.306
Um, did we ever go here?

10:41.340 --> 10:42.408
[PAPER RUSTLES]

10:45.277 --> 10:46.412
Oh, wow.

10:47.579 --> 10:49.615
Cedar Creek?

10:49.648 --> 10:50.649
Where did you find this?

10:50.682 --> 10:52.985
Um, Dad kept it.

10:55.487 --> 10:56.789
Oh.

11:00.792 --> 11:02.795
Did something happen there?

11:05.196 --> 11:08.167
I don't know.
We went there,
the three of us.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.036
Went camping.
It's nice.

11:10.502 --> 11:11.370
Is that it?

11:12.938 --> 11:15.074
Henry, what are you
looking for?

11:15.874 --> 11:18.209
He's my dad.
I want to know about him.

11:18.243 --> 11:20.612
It's just this thing
happens with Bill Boone,

11:20.645 --> 11:22.747
and then all the sudden,
you want to know

11:22.781 --> 11:24.249
everything there is to know
about your dad,

11:24.283 --> 11:27.019
as if he's the only person
who can fix this.

11:27.586 --> 11:28.921
Fix what?

11:31.156 --> 11:33.925
Did something happen?
Did Bill Boone hurt you?

11:33.959 --> 11:34.894
What?

11:35.694 --> 11:36.962
Would you tell me if he did?

11:36.995 --> 11:39.598
Why would I lie
about getting hurt?

11:39.631 --> 11:40.900
You have before.

11:42.334 --> 11:43.202
Oh.

11:43.702 --> 11:44.836
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.

11:44.869 --> 11:47.339
So by "fix this,"
you mean me?

11:47.372 --> 11:48.907
You want to fix me?

11:48.940 --> 11:50.442
No, that's not
what I'm saying.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.245
Yeah.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.245
Uh, Henry, please.

11:53.278 --> 11:54.780
It's fine, Mom.

11:57.349 --> 11:58.951
[SIGHS] Shit.

11:59.384 --> 12:01.353
[SNIFFLING]

12:01.386 --> 12:04.323
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

12:10.529 --> 12:12.164
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

12:17.036 --> 12:20.072
<i> [ON YOUR WINGS</i> PLAYING]

12:26.811 --> 12:30.014
<i> ♪ God, there is gold</i>

12:30.048 --> 12:33.519
<i> ♪ Hidden deep in the ground</i>

12:36.788 --> 12:40.392
<i> ♪ God, there's a hangman</i>

12:40.426 --> 12:43.429
<i> ♪ That wants to come round</i>

12:45.897 --> 12:48.467
<i>♪ How we rise when we're born</i>

12:48.500 --> 12:50.935
<i>♪ Like the ravens in the corn</i>

12:50.969 --> 12:53.271
<i>♪ On their wings, on our knees</i>

12:53.305 --> 12:56.541
<i> ♪ Crawling careless
From the sea</i>

12:56.574 --> 12:59.544
<i> ♪ God, give us love</i>

12:59.578 --> 13:02.782
<i> ♪ In the time that we have ♪</i>

13:09.554 --> 13:10.856
[WHOOSHING]

13:10.890 --> 13:13.993
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

13:19.898 --> 13:21.934
Hank, I could use your help.

13:24.436 --> 13:26.071
HENRY: Dad!

13:26.104 --> 13:28.374
I know where we are now.

13:29.040 --> 13:30.643
It's Cedar Creek, right?

13:30.676 --> 13:33.012
We came here together
when I was little.

13:36.482 --> 13:37.516
Did you find
a good stick, Hank?

13:38.784 --> 13:40.419
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

13:44.355 --> 13:45.958
Uh, yeah.

13:48.527 --> 13:49.495
Come on.

13:55.500 --> 13:56.502
[SIMON EXHALES HEAVILY]

13:58.204 --> 13:59.505
[BIRD CAWING]

14:06.244 --> 14:07.279
This happened.

14:08.180 --> 14:10.216
I'm dreaming about this
for a reason,

14:10.249 --> 14:12.284
because you're trying
to tell me something, right?

14:15.520 --> 14:17.989
Huh. We're missing one.

14:18.022 --> 14:20.893
A seven, you're missing
a seven of hearts.

14:21.894 --> 14:23.262
SIMON: Yep.

14:24.329 --> 14:27.233
Seven of hearts,
but it's okay.

14:27.899 --> 14:30.169
We will make our own.

14:35.140 --> 14:37.342
Dad, I need your help.

14:37.375 --> 14:39.311
I need you to tell me
where you are.

14:42.814 --> 14:44.350
I'm right here, Hank.

14:44.883 --> 14:46.018
So is Mom.

14:46.051 --> 14:48.053
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

14:49.888 --> 14:51.356
Careful,
you're gonna burn it.

14:51.390 --> 14:52.391
CLEO: Well, you gotta
burn it a little bit.

14:52.424 --> 14:54.326
That's what brings out
the flavor.

14:55.327 --> 14:56.428
See, Hank?

14:56.995 --> 14:58.330
It's our special card.

14:59.665 --> 15:01.433
There's no other one
like it.

15:05.871 --> 15:07.706
YOUNG HENRY:
He's not here anymore.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.141
Neither are you.

15:10.142 --> 15:12.344
You need to wake up.

15:15.047 --> 15:16.448
[BIRDS CAWING]

15:18.484 --> 15:20.653
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

15:49.948 --> 15:53.052
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

16:26.618 --> 16:28.020
Dad.

17:13.232 --> 17:14.500
Dad?

17:42.761 --> 17:44.495
Ah!

17:44.529 --> 17:46.465
[GROANING]

17:56.074 --> 17:58.210
[CHUCKLES]

18:04.817 --> 18:06.718
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

18:10.722 --> 18:12.157
Mm.

18:12.190 --> 18:13.325
I'll get it.

18:15.126 --> 18:16.628
I got it. I got it.

18:18.930 --> 18:19.998
Yeah.

18:20.031 --> 18:22.300
Thank you.

18:20.031 --> 18:22.300
You're welcome.

18:22.333 --> 18:25.570
So I was actually
the laundry guy in my house,

18:25.603 --> 18:28.173
and baking soda
will get that stain out.

18:28.206 --> 18:29.941
What is baking soda?

18:29.974 --> 18:32.244
Uh... Oh, it, uh...

18:32.277 --> 18:33.578
it's, like...
It's, like, for cooking,

18:33.611 --> 18:35.447
and they put it
in toothpaste and...

18:35.947 --> 18:37.282
What is toothpaste?

18:38.550 --> 18:40.618
Oh, you're messing
with me, right?

18:40.652 --> 18:42.521
[LAUGHTER]

18:42.554 --> 18:44.856
We're not all
as sheltered as you
may think, Lucas Boone.

18:44.890 --> 18:47.926
Go easy on me.
I'm new here.

18:47.959 --> 18:49.294
I gotta go.

18:55.601 --> 18:56.869
How you doing?

19:04.009 --> 19:06.144
Lucas seems
at peace here,

19:06.178 --> 19:08.413
especially
in your presence.

19:10.382 --> 19:13.385
I wish my father
agreed with you.

19:13.418 --> 19:16.988
Isaiah still can't see
beyond Bill Boone's shadow.

19:17.021 --> 19:18.924
He will learn that Lucas
is his own man.

19:20.525 --> 19:23.529
He says to know the son,
one only has to look
to the father.

19:24.462 --> 19:26.832
Are we not all
born of Adam?

19:26.865 --> 19:29.268
Lucas has chosen a godly path.

19:29.301 --> 19:31.503
He, too, is in service
of our Lord.

19:38.610 --> 19:39.444
<i> ♪ I...</i>

19:39.477 --> 19:43.048
<i> ♪ Day I, day I, day I die</i>

19:43.081 --> 19:44.950
<i> ♪ I'm not ready to go</i>

19:44.983 --> 19:46.485
<i> ♪ Day I</i>

19:46.518 --> 19:49.253
<i> ♪ I'm not ready
To go, go, go ♪</i>

19:49.287 --> 19:50.889
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

20:02.000 --> 20:03.468
Sure, Henry, come on in.

20:03.501 --> 20:04.803
I think I found my dad.

20:06.137 --> 20:07.438
You had another dream?

20:07.471 --> 20:10.642
Yeah, but this time,
I woke up

20:10.675 --> 20:13.345
in the middle of it,
and I was somewhere else.

20:14.446 --> 20:17.382
Like, my mind has been
dreaming of one place,

20:17.415 --> 20:20.852
and my body has been
taking me to another.

20:20.885 --> 20:22.453
And your dad was there?

20:22.487 --> 20:24.923
No, but he's been there,
I think.

20:24.956 --> 20:28.092
And he might be back,
so I need to talk to Townes,

20:28.125 --> 20:29.728
but he won't answer my texts.

20:29.761 --> 20:31.330
Can you give me
a ride over there?

20:33.965 --> 20:35.300
What?

20:36.434 --> 20:38.537
When we went to Colgate,

20:39.937 --> 20:41.506
Townes had a breakdown,

20:41.539 --> 20:43.375
and it was
really scary, Henry.

20:43.408 --> 20:45.377
He's not okay.

20:43.408 --> 20:45.377
What do you mean?

20:46.712 --> 20:47.980
Townes met the hacker.

20:48.547 --> 20:49.581
What?

20:51.450 --> 20:53.752
Okay, what did he say?
Who is he?

20:54.953 --> 20:56.421
Some bald guy named Sam.

20:56.455 --> 20:57.989
I guess he just
wanted to talk to you.

20:58.022 --> 21:01.325
But Townes feels like he's
failed you as a sidekick.

21:01.359 --> 21:03.795
You need to give him
some space.

21:05.163 --> 21:09.267
I mean, I didn't ask him
to do that.

21:09.301 --> 21:10.769
But these things
that are happening,

21:10.802 --> 21:13.538
they're not just
happening to you.

21:13.571 --> 21:15.406
Okay, it's a lot for anyone,

21:15.440 --> 21:18.543
especially someone who needs
a schedule and routine.

21:18.576 --> 21:19.878
Okay.

21:25.517 --> 21:28.586
If this hacker guy
knows something about my dad,

21:28.619 --> 21:32.123
like, the thing is,
I need to talk to him.

21:32.157 --> 21:33.625
I just do.

21:35.193 --> 21:36.260
And you know what?

21:36.294 --> 21:37.895
That'll show Townes

21:37.929 --> 21:40.231
that he's, like,
a good sidekick or whatever,

21:40.264 --> 21:42.600
thus helping him.

21:42.634 --> 21:45.604
Uh-huh. And how would
the hacker know
anything about your dad?

21:45.637 --> 21:48.873
He sent the video of that guy
in the sleep study,

21:48.907 --> 21:50.875
and I read my dad's journal.

21:50.909 --> 21:51.810
I think he's a part of it.

21:51.843 --> 21:54.979
Yeah, that guy,
Dominick Babtiste,

21:55.013 --> 21:56.014
he's dead.

21:57.115 --> 21:59.685
And the hacker said
Nikolai killed him.

22:00.952 --> 22:01.987
He wouldn't have done that.

22:03.588 --> 22:06.324
The guy who dissolved
Bill Boone's body in acid?

22:06.357 --> 22:08.293
Who left your mom to die?

22:08.326 --> 22:10.028
Jenna, I really need
to talk to Townes, so...

22:10.061 --> 22:11.262
No, he can't handle it.

22:11.296 --> 22:12.730
Jenna, I will...

22:12.763 --> 22:14.933
Ugh, I will apologize
to him or whatever,

22:14.966 --> 22:17.102
but I just...
I need this.

22:17.135 --> 22:19.470
I need this, okay?

22:19.504 --> 22:21.573
This Sam guy might be
the only person

22:21.606 --> 22:22.908
who can tell me the truth.

22:24.976 --> 22:25.977
Please?

22:31.182 --> 22:32.451
[KNOCKING]

22:38.290 --> 22:40.425
Hi, Mrs. Linderman.

22:40.459 --> 22:42.427
I'm sorry, girls,
but Townes isn't home
right now.

22:42.460 --> 22:44.062
He's with his therapist.

22:44.096 --> 22:47.165
He's having
a challenging week.

22:47.198 --> 22:49.000
But I'll tell him
you stopped by.

22:49.033 --> 22:50.135
He'll be happy to hear it.

22:50.168 --> 22:52.337
Okay, thanks.
Sorry to bother you.

22:52.370 --> 22:54.539
You know, I...
[CHUCKLES]

22:54.572 --> 22:58.109
I actually think
that I left my textbook
in his room.

22:58.142 --> 23:01.813
We just have a really
big test tomorrow for physics.

23:01.847 --> 23:04.516
So do you think that I could
just run up and grab it?

23:14.159 --> 23:15.259
[KEYS CLACKING]

23:15.293 --> 23:16.828
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

23:16.861 --> 23:17.962
This feels wrong.

23:17.995 --> 23:19.597
Townes would hate
that we're even in here
without him.

23:19.631 --> 23:22.334
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

23:19.631 --> 23:22.334
Well,
go if you want, Jenna.

23:22.367 --> 23:25.536
Or stay and help me
guess his password.

23:25.570 --> 23:27.906
Is "sidekick"
two words or one?

23:27.939 --> 23:30.075
It's not going to be
that obvious.

23:33.945 --> 23:36.113
Well, then, Jenna,

23:36.147 --> 23:39.418
help me think like Townes.

23:40.551 --> 23:43.354
What is that thing called?

23:43.387 --> 23:45.891
Uh, I don't know,
the<i> Millennium Falcon?</i>

23:50.428 --> 23:51.496
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

23:51.530 --> 23:52.931
[HENRY SIGHS]

23:53.264 --> 23:54.633
Oh, shit.

23:56.034 --> 23:57.702
Oh, shit, Jenna.

23:59.937 --> 24:01.206
It's Sam.

24:04.909 --> 24:05.911
What should I say?

24:07.211 --> 24:08.646
This whole thing is so creepy.

24:08.679 --> 24:10.515
How does he even know
that it's you?

24:12.183 --> 24:14.619
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

24:20.892 --> 24:22.360
Hi.

24:22.393 --> 24:23.795
Um...

24:25.096 --> 24:27.064
I'm looking for Simon Coles.

24:27.098 --> 24:30.535
He was in a sleep study
like Dominick Babtiste,

24:30.568 --> 24:33.605
but it was years ago,
before I was born.

24:41.279 --> 24:42.514
What do you want?

24:47.419 --> 24:48.887
I can take you
anywhere you want.

24:50.922 --> 24:53.091
[CHIMES]

25:00.565 --> 25:02.534
[EXHALES]

25:06.337 --> 25:07.605
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

25:07.639 --> 25:09.808
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

25:13.911 --> 25:15.113
[SIGHS]

25:18.349 --> 25:20.018
Yes?

25:20.051 --> 25:21.386
I need to talk to Clay.

25:21.419 --> 25:22.887
Is he home?

25:22.921 --> 25:24.388
No, he's out.

25:24.422 --> 25:25.991
Do you know
when he'll be back?

25:27.258 --> 25:28.293
I'm sorry, who are you?

25:28.893 --> 25:29.961
Cleo Coles.

25:32.163 --> 25:34.199
Uh, please, come in.

25:44.709 --> 25:46.278
Let's sit down.

25:51.916 --> 25:54.585
Can I get you
something to drink?

25:54.619 --> 25:57.121
Some water or... chardonnay?

25:57.154 --> 25:58.890
I've got some open.

26:05.129 --> 26:09.567
When I heard what happened
with Bill, I...

26:09.600 --> 26:12.137
I prayed for your recovery
every day.

26:12.170 --> 26:13.939
Our whole congregation did.

26:20.478 --> 26:23.481
Uh, you said that
you came to see Clay.

26:23.515 --> 26:25.884
May I ask what it is
that you wanted to tell him?

26:29.621 --> 26:32.923
To go fuck himself.

26:32.957 --> 26:36.794
I think that's what I was
hoping... to tell him.

26:36.827 --> 26:38.529
Okay, I think you should leave.

26:38.563 --> 26:40.198
I understand
what Bill did to you,
but...

26:40.231 --> 26:42.000
You son assaulted my daughter.

26:44.802 --> 26:47.205
He forced himself on her,

26:47.238 --> 26:49.474
and now she's not who she was.

26:49.507 --> 26:50.608
He took that from her.

26:50.642 --> 26:52.777
He fought to take that
from her.

27:01.285 --> 27:02.653
What...

27:02.686 --> 27:04.255
What do you want me
to do about it?

27:04.622 --> 27:06.191
[SCOFFS]

27:07.025 --> 27:08.059
Did you know?

27:08.793 --> 27:09.828
No.

27:12.597 --> 27:14.899
But I'm not surprised.
He's very angry.

27:17.835 --> 27:19.970
I won't let him...

27:20.004 --> 27:23.508
God, I will not let him
get away with it.

27:23.541 --> 27:25.110
Is your daughter
pressing charges?

27:28.679 --> 27:30.382
That's not what she wants.

27:32.016 --> 27:34.853
I've been taking Clay
to church.

27:34.886 --> 27:36.521
My husband's a pastor.

27:36.554 --> 27:38.456
Bill didn't raise
the boys with religion.

27:38.489 --> 27:42.159
But... Clay is just...
he's hesitant.

27:42.193 --> 27:43.328
He's closed off.

27:45.362 --> 27:47.432
But I will push him.

27:47.465 --> 27:49.434
I will make him repent
for his sins.

27:49.467 --> 27:51.369
That's not gonna change
what he did.

27:55.005 --> 27:57.142
I could try to make him
apologize to her.

27:57.975 --> 28:00.611
[SIGHS] I doubt
he'll listen to me.

28:00.644 --> 28:03.848
The truth is, he doesn't
respect me very much.

28:09.720 --> 28:11.256
When I left,

28:12.456 --> 28:14.759
Clay was only nine.

28:17.128 --> 28:19.464
Henry doesn't want
to talk to him.

28:27.538 --> 28:29.441
Tell me
what she needs.

28:31.376 --> 28:32.977
I don't know.

28:35.780 --> 28:37.248
I don't know.

28:40.351 --> 28:43.388
[SOBBING]

28:47.158 --> 28:50.261
I've never been a part
of anything like this before,

28:51.095 --> 28:52.663
making something
so important.

28:52.697 --> 28:54.132
[CHUCKLES]

28:57.468 --> 28:59.170
It's so quiet now.

29:00.638 --> 29:02.940
I can imagine
once a family moves in,

29:02.974 --> 29:06.177
full of energy,
kids racing down
the stairs.

29:07.678 --> 29:09.781
Sounds like a good life.

29:10.682 --> 29:12.450
It's a simple life.

29:13.684 --> 29:15.887
Nothing like
the exciting one you lived.

29:18.422 --> 29:19.958
Do you miss it?

29:23.427 --> 29:24.796
Not at all.

29:26.964 --> 29:30.101
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

29:41.445 --> 29:43.081
Can I kiss you?

29:57.327 --> 29:58.463
[GASPS]

29:58.496 --> 29:59.931
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

30:02.433 --> 30:04.702
Listen, this was all me.
She didn't do anything!

30:04.736 --> 30:07.305
Father, please,
I'm sorry.

30:04.736 --> 30:07.305
She's...

30:07.338 --> 30:09.040
LUCAS: Hey! Hey!

30:09.073 --> 30:10.975
Hey, hey, leave...
leave her alone!

30:11.008 --> 30:13.144
Do not touch me again.

30:11.008 --> 30:13.144
Listen, I did this!

30:13.177 --> 30:14.779
If you wanna punish someone,
then do it to me.

30:14.812 --> 30:16.514
I am offering myself.

30:16.548 --> 30:18.382
ISAIAH: You may be
the wolf among us,

30:18.416 --> 30:20.985
but it is her responsibility
to resist your temptation.

30:21.018 --> 30:23.120
We kissed!
She's not a fucking nun!

30:23.153 --> 30:25.857
Brothers, my daughter has
strayed from the Lord's path.

30:25.890 --> 30:28.659
I ask you to bear witness
to her repentance.

30:28.692 --> 30:29.727
SUSANNAH: Dear Merciful God...

30:29.760 --> 30:31.261
No, you don't need
to do this.

30:31.295 --> 30:33.497
Stop! She's not
your fucking property!

30:33.530 --> 30:34.866
No, come with me.

30:34.899 --> 30:38.169
Lucas, Lucas, please,
do as I say.

30:38.202 --> 30:40.771
I have allowed myself
to become preoccupied

30:40.804 --> 30:42.140
with my own wants.

30:42.173 --> 30:44.642
I confess before you
my complicity

30:44.675 --> 30:46.611
in the sins of this world.

30:46.644 --> 30:49.514
<i> [TAKE A WALK</i> PLAYING]

30:52.316 --> 30:54.218
<i> ♪ Tough break, and you
Broke it all right in two ♪</i>

30:54.252 --> 30:55.987
Nice Discman.

30:57.822 --> 30:59.090
What?

30:59.123 --> 31:00.858
I just said, nice Discman.

31:00.892 --> 31:02.993
Oh, yeah.

31:03.027 --> 31:05.996
It has
dynamic bass boost, so...

31:06.029 --> 31:07.931
[CHUCKLES] Rad, rad.

31:06.029 --> 31:07.931
Yeah.

31:07.965 --> 31:09.834
You good? I can take
that if you want.

31:09.867 --> 31:11.335
Oh, I got it.

31:09.867 --> 31:11.335
All right.

31:11.369 --> 31:12.436
[MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY
OVER HEADPHONES]

31:12.470 --> 31:14.906
<i> ♪ Cost of taking a walk
With you</i>

31:15.506 --> 31:17.942
<i> ♪ I can tell myself</i>

31:17.975 --> 31:20.644
<i> ♪ This is for all
Concerned's health</i>

31:20.678 --> 31:24.481
<i> ♪ And I may yet dot that I ♪</i>

31:24.515 --> 31:26.251
Jesus Christ.

31:30.755 --> 31:32.924
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

31:34.491 --> 31:35.693
What are you doing here?

31:35.727 --> 31:37.595
People who found your mess
in Sri Lanka

31:37.629 --> 31:38.829
are on the move.

31:38.862 --> 31:40.265
I tracked them
to another safe house.

31:40.898 --> 31:42.667
Hoping you could help.

31:42.700 --> 31:44.335
They're tracking you,

31:44.368 --> 31:47.705
gathering information
on everywhere you've lived
for the past decade.

31:47.738 --> 31:49.774
Whoever it is,
they know who you are

31:49.807 --> 31:52.443
and what you did with Bill.

31:52.476 --> 31:55.313
So you need to tell me
if you've had
any contact with them.

31:58.349 --> 32:00.551
It's not a multiple choice
question.

32:06.958 --> 32:08.493
Yeah, um...

32:09.593 --> 32:11.663
I already told you
I don't know who it is.

32:14.665 --> 32:16.668
I should go.

32:16.701 --> 32:18.436
I can't protect you
if you lie to me.

32:19.904 --> 32:22.640
Maybe they're
protecting me from you.

32:22.673 --> 32:24.775
Is that really
what you think?

32:24.809 --> 32:27.611
Because I've been hanging
around this shit town
busting my ass...

32:27.645 --> 32:30.147
Yeah, but you never tell me
what's going on.

32:30.181 --> 32:32.616
You just tell me to, like,
blindly trust you.

32:32.650 --> 32:34.384
Actions build trust.

32:34.418 --> 32:36.620
I've only acted
in your best interest.

32:36.653 --> 32:38.089
For now.

32:39.123 --> 32:41.092
Maybe you're just waiting
for the right time

32:41.125 --> 32:43.194
to, like, lock me up
in a room somewhere

32:43.227 --> 32:45.496
and study me
and watch me sleep
and fucking torture me.

32:46.831 --> 32:48.666
Where'd you get that idea?

32:51.069 --> 32:52.503
I don't know.

32:53.438 --> 32:54.973
It's just a guess...

32:56.074 --> 32:58.710
based on your
general dark vibe.

33:00.577 --> 33:02.113
Tell me I'm wrong.

33:04.749 --> 33:06.985
I don't know,
tell me the truth.

33:08.686 --> 33:10.288
[INAUDIBLE]

33:37.281 --> 33:40.385
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

34:05.676 --> 34:07.178
[DEVICE BEEPS]

34:39.744 --> 34:41.745
ESTHER: You showed mercy,

34:41.779 --> 34:43.614
and that should be rewarded.

34:44.815 --> 34:46.684
Remove your shoes.

34:50.420 --> 34:51.355
Please.

34:59.630 --> 35:01.833
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

35:34.866 --> 35:38.802
Jesus washed his disciples'
feet to honor them.

35:38.836 --> 35:40.705
I shouldn't be honored
right now.

35:43.206 --> 35:44.408
This is my fault.

35:44.441 --> 35:46.744
Susannah's sin is not lust.

35:46.777 --> 35:49.279
It is the hubris
of disobeying her father.

35:49.313 --> 35:53.217
You showed fortitude
and empathy.

35:55.386 --> 35:57.955
Isaiah didn't show mercy

35:57.988 --> 36:00.290
or humility or...
or any of that.

36:00.324 --> 36:02.293
She and I,
we did the same thing.

36:05.295 --> 36:08.131
The burden of sin most often
falls upon the woman.

36:08.165 --> 36:10.268
Well, that doesn't
make it right.

36:14.038 --> 36:16.240
I don't want her
to get hurt again.

36:41.932 --> 36:43.301
LUCAS: Fentanyl.

36:46.169 --> 36:48.339
If this were found
in Isaiah's house,

36:48.372 --> 36:51.108
he would be forced
from the church.

36:51.141 --> 36:52.944
Susannah would be free.

36:58.382 --> 37:00.718
This stuff has hurt
so many people already.

37:01.718 --> 37:04.054
Isaiah will not let
this community evolve

37:04.087 --> 37:05.889
while he remains
a leader here.

37:05.922 --> 37:08.492
I could talk to Susannah.
I can see what she wants.

37:08.525 --> 37:10.394
She may not know
until you show her.

37:12.396 --> 37:16.433
God is merciful,
but he is also just.

37:16.466 --> 37:19.570
Remember the Great Flood
that cleansed the old world

37:19.603 --> 37:22.340
so the faithful could build
a better one.

37:41.925 --> 37:44.595
YVETTE: [OVER PHONE]
<i> When will you hear
back from the review board?</i>

37:45.329 --> 37:47.697
It might take some time.

37:47.731 --> 37:50.734
YVETTE:<i> You told them
what you told me?</i>

37:50.767 --> 37:54.171
Don't worry about it.
I'll be fine.

37:54.205 --> 37:57.040
<i> Why are you sitting
in your car?</i>

37:57.074 --> 37:58.342
I'm meeting
a friend for dinner.

37:58.375 --> 37:59.744
I'm just early.

38:02.412 --> 38:05.349
<i> I was thinking about Ortez.</i>

38:06.850 --> 38:08.318
<i> After he died,</i>

38:08.351 --> 38:10.855
<i> you told me you'd still
see him sometimes.</i>

38:13.724 --> 38:14.625
I got over that.

38:14.658 --> 38:16.226
<i> Right, because the way
I remember it,</i>

38:16.260 --> 38:19.830
<i> you just left, and now you're
seeing bodies in the road.</i>

38:19.863 --> 38:22.232
This wasn't like that.

38:22.266 --> 38:23.433
This was real.

38:23.466 --> 38:25.402
<i> Maybe you should
come home for a while,</i>

38:25.435 --> 38:28.105
<i> just until the board
makes their decision.</i>

38:28.138 --> 38:29.373
<i> Recharge a bit.</i>

38:29.406 --> 38:30.541
<i> If you want,
I can talk to Dad.</i>

38:32.610 --> 38:35.112
Yvette, I gotta go.
My friend is here.

38:35.146 --> 38:36.981
<i> Okay, let...</i>

38:37.014 --> 38:38.783
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

38:51.761 --> 38:54.698
HENRY: Ugh, he should have
been here, like,
half an hour ago.

38:54.731 --> 38:57.568
Maybe Sam could, like,
get a message to my dad

38:57.601 --> 39:00.104
that I'm okay
and that I'm, like,

39:00.137 --> 39:01.706
looking for him
or something.

39:02.172 --> 39:03.474
What do you think?

39:05.308 --> 39:06.544
Nice suit.

39:07.878 --> 39:09.713
It is nice.

39:09.746 --> 39:12.549
HENRY: Okay, shit.

39:09.746 --> 39:12.549
JENNA: What?

39:12.582 --> 39:15.686
Just because
you're in a good mood,
everybody has to be?

39:15.719 --> 39:18.455
So one of us always
has to be an asshole?

39:18.488 --> 39:19.890
You're the expert.

39:19.923 --> 39:20.958
Jenna.

39:22.159 --> 39:23.427
Fine.

39:24.895 --> 39:27.764
You probably don't care,
but the dance is on Saturday,

39:27.798 --> 39:32.803
and Zach is being
super sweet, like always.

39:32.836 --> 39:36.407
But I don't think
that I want to go with him.

39:36.440 --> 39:38.409
And that sucks,

39:39.443 --> 39:43.313
'cause he likes me a lot,
and I should like him.

39:43.346 --> 39:45.582
I should be happy.

39:45.616 --> 39:49.820
But my trip to Colgate
was just so... intense

39:49.854 --> 39:52.789
and confusing.

39:52.822 --> 39:55.792
And everyone
just presumes I'm okay,

39:55.825 --> 39:58.829
that I'm always okay,
but what if I'm not?

39:58.862 --> 40:01.599
[VOICE BREAKING]
And then my dad
just announces

40:01.632 --> 40:05.335
that he's getting remarried
to your mom, which is fine.

40:05.369 --> 40:07.738
I mean, you know I really
do love you guys.

40:07.771 --> 40:10.741
But I just...
I just feel like

40:10.775 --> 40:13.911
the family that we had before
is being erased...

40:14.911 --> 40:18.082
like, she won't
exist anymore, and it...

40:18.115 --> 40:19.450
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

40:23.954 --> 40:25.790
Man, Jenna...

40:29.326 --> 40:31.562
Nobody is trying
to erase anybody.

40:34.898 --> 40:38.002
You know, I never wanted
to move to Reston.

40:39.169 --> 40:40.571
[SCOFFS]

40:41.906 --> 40:44.108
Excuse me
while I die of shock.

40:44.775 --> 40:45.843
Yeah.

40:47.044 --> 40:49.980
Yeah, I was pushing
for somewhere warmer...

40:51.448 --> 40:52.850
Like a city...

40:54.184 --> 40:55.653
Or, like...

40:55.686 --> 40:58.121
I don't know, anywhere else
really would have
been fine for me.

40:58.155 --> 40:59.457
[CHUCKLES]

41:01.391 --> 41:04.295
But I never
get to have a say

41:04.328 --> 41:06.664
in where we go
or who we live with,

41:06.697 --> 41:09.767
so... I kinda get it.

41:14.205 --> 41:16.607
But I don't know, this time
it could be a lot worse.

41:30.220 --> 41:32.523
Maybe Sam got lost.

41:35.993 --> 41:37.294
[SNIFFLES]

41:37.328 --> 41:39.029
No, he's not coming.

41:43.333 --> 41:44.602
[SIGHS]

41:47.171 --> 41:48.973
[DOOR OPENS]

41:50.073 --> 41:51.175
Lucas?

41:51.575 --> 41:53.077
[DOOR CLOSES]

41:57.614 --> 41:58.849
If my father
finds me here...

41:58.882 --> 42:00.784
Yeah, yeah, I know. I know.
I know. I'm sorry.

42:00.817 --> 42:01.919
I, um...

42:11.528 --> 42:13.764
SUSANNAH:
Why do you have fentanyl?

42:17.100 --> 42:20.704
Esther says that this
is the only way that
he's gonna leave you alone.

42:22.272 --> 42:24.474
